# Coffee 2.0 - Temporary Instructions File
# Below you will find the Text Syntax to create Command Parameters

Types:

  <Required Parameter>
  [Optional Parameter]
  (Parameters in the Same Level)
  {Child Parameter}

Special Symbols:

  : Attribute Value Start
  ; Attribute Value End
  && AND Operator
  || OR Operator
  ! NOT Operator
  "" String
  () Boolean Brackets

Keywords:

  Name
  Required
    Role
    Permission
  Syntax
    Equals
    Contains
    User Mention
    Role Mention
    Text Channel
    Voice Channel

Notes:

  Name is a mandatory attribute
  If no Requirement is specified, consider as no Requirement to check
  If no Syntax is specified, consider as no Syntax to check
  If one of the parameters in its level is Optional, every parameter in that level should be Optional
  If no level specified (No { }) consider as first level

Examples:

<Name: Sample;>
<Name: Sample; {[Name: Child One; Syntax Equals: "Banana" || Syntax Equals: "Coconut"] [Name: Child Two; Syntax Contains: "Elbow" {<Name: Coconut>}]}>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Parameter Syntax 2.0

ID: 0;
NAME: Name;
TYPE: Required;
CONDITION: Role = Role Name; Mention = False; Syntax = Equals "Text";
CHILD: 1,2;

Note: By default conditions are set to be AND. If one condition returns false, the parameter's validity is false.

ID: 1